# Module creation in Cursor

Shared agent prompts live in `.claude/agents/` (single source of truth — do not fork).

## When the user wants a module

1. **Unclear paper / kind** → Task `paper-scout` (read `.claude/agents/paper-scout.md`); route SNP / PGS / PGx.
2. **SNP solo** → Task `module-creator` (`.claude/agents/module-creator.md`).
3. **PGS** → Task `pgs-module-creator` (`.claude/agents/pgs-module-creator.md`).
4. **PGx** → Task `pgx-module-creator` (`.claude/agents/pgx-module-creator.md`).
5. **SNP high-stakes / full team** → parallel Task `researcher` (×2–3), then Task `reviewer`, then synthesize as PI.
6. Or slash **create-module** (SNP team flow).

## After writing specs

```bash
uv run dna-agents validate <spec_dir>/
uv run dna-agents compile <spec_dir>/ -o <output_dir>/
```

Use MCP `validate_spec` / `compile_module` / `get_spec_format` when connected. BioContext KB for Ensembl + EuropePMC.

## Portable paths only

Use repo-relative `uv run …`. Never hardcode machine-absolute paths or personal API keys in committed files.
